<P>Episcopal Charities and Community Services (ECCS) is a network of 13 social service agencies organized as official agencies of the Diocese of Chicago, and linked through the ECCS central office at the Episcopal Church Center.  Their joint mission is to respond to the social welfare needs of residents in Metropolitan Chicago and Rockford, Illinois.</p>
<P>
The ECCS central office serves as a resource developer and monitor for the individual agencies, and also monitors and reports on aspects of public policy on behalf of the Diocese of Chicago and member agencies.</p>

